.TH "xvip_of_get_format" 9 "xvip_of_get_format" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xvip_of_get_format \- Parse a device tree node and return format information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct xvip_video_format *" xvip_of_get_format
.BI "(struct device_node *node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "node" 12
the device tree node
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read the xlnx,video-format, xlnx,video-width and xlnx,cfa-pattern properties
from the device tree \fInode\fP passed as an argument and return the corresponding
format information.
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the format information structure corresponding to the
format name and width, or ERR_PTR if no corresponding format can be found.
